<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-512] The Lustre Operations Manual does not document the append_pool or append_stripe_count options</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-512</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The Lustre Operations Manual does not document the append_pool or append_stripe_count options.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=adilger&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;adilger&quot;&gt;adilger&lt;/a&gt; wrote in the Linux Lustre Client #general Slack:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;note that there is a special &quot;append&quot; layout, see &quot;&lt;tt&gt;mdd.&amp;#42;.append_pool&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; and &quot;&lt;tt&gt;mdd.&amp;#42;.append_stripe_count&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;, because often append files are logs and have different allocation needs, and also to avoid the &quot;append instantiates all components&quot; issue that is tracked under &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12738&quot; title=&quot;PFL: append of PFL file should not instantiate full layout&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-12738&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-12738&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;</description>
